sql:
SELECT AVG(beer_servings) AS AverageBeerServings
FROM datasets
WHERE data_collection_year = 2022 AND data_source_id IS NULL;

external_knowledge:
- "European countries" refers to those located in the geographical region of Europe;
- "Highly accurate" refers to a data accuracy level categorized as 'high' in the database;
- "Recently released" means reports that were published on or after January 1, 2023.

- "first user" refers to the user with the update ID of 1;
- "nations" refers to the countries in the database;
- "data collected in a known year" means the data collection year is not null.
